    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Power Cylinders - Inspection - Piston
        Rings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Piston Rings</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, whenever a piston is removed from a cylinder, replace the piston rings.
                    Faulty piston rings cannot always be detected by visual inspection. Therefore, if the rings are
                    replaced, the cylinder sleeves need to be replaced as well.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the new piston rings for cleanliness. Use a suitable solvent to clean the piston
                rings if necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26508inspect04.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH04/H04006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking piston ring end gap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push the piston ring down into the cylinder bore. Make sure that the piston ring is
                perpendicular to the cylinder wall.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge to measure the end gap between the ends of each piston ring.</para>
            <para>Discard any piston ring that does not meet specifications.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
